  "texts": [
    "Building upon this insight, we formalize AAR by presenting key implementation details which enables AAR to balance robustness and stability.",
    "PreliminariesIn traditional anomaly detection, it is typically assumed that the training dataset is clean, consisting solely of normal instances.",
    "Let this clean dataset be denoted by D n:= {(x i, y i)} Nn i=1, where y i = 0 indicates a normal sample and N n is the number of such instances.",
    "However, in real-world scenarios, datasets are often contaminated by abnormal instances.",
    "Let the set of abnormal samples be denoted by D a:= {(x i, y i)} Na i=1, where y i = 1 indicates an anomaly and N a is the number of such samples."
